Linux Basic Commands Cheat Sheet

1. echo - Print text
Syntax:
echo "Hello World"
echo $HOME
echo -n "Hello"
echo -e "Hello\nWorld"
Memory Trick: echo = say something loudly

2. whoami - Show current user
Syntax:
whoami
Memory Trick: Who am I?

3. id - Show user and group information
Syntax:
id
id -u
id -g
id -un
id -gn
Memory Trick: id = identity

4. cd - Change directory
Examples:
cd Documents
cd ..
cd ~
cd /
cd -
Memory Trick: Change Directory

5. pwd - Print working directory
Syntax:
pwd
Memory Trick: Present Working Directory

6. touch - Create empty files
Examples:
touch file.txt
touch a.txt b.txt c.txt
touch file{1..5}.txt
Memory Trick: touch a file into existence

7. mkdir - Make directory
Examples:
mkdir Projects
mkdir dir1 dir2 dir3
mkdir -p web/html/css
Memory Trick: make directory

8. ls - List files and directories
Examples:
ls
ls -l
ls -a
ls -lh
ls -la
ls -ltr
ls -R
Memory Trick: list

9. cp - Copy files/directories
Examples:
cp file1.txt file2.txt
cp file.txt Documents/
cp -r Folder Backup
Options:
-r  recursive
-i  interactive
-v  verbose
Memory Trick: copy

10. mv - Move or rename
Examples:
mv old.txt new.txt
mv file.txt Documents/
mv *.txt Backup/
Memory Trick: move

11. rm - Remove files/directories
Examples:
rm file.txt
rm a.txt b.txt
rm -r Folder
rm -rf Folder
Warning:
Never run: rm -rf /
Memory Trick: remove

12. rmdir - Remove empty directories
Examples:
rmdir Test
rmdir -p a/b/c
Memory Trick: remove directory

